h3#Application Backend
br
h4#descrip_title Oracle Virtualbox + Vagrant
p#descrip_text We virtualize a Web Server using Virtualbox and Vagrant so the whole team have the same ubuntu environment to work with.
br
h4#descrip_title Nginx + Chef + Unicorn
p#descrip_text  We use the chef script to set up a Nginx Server and listen on the Unicorn socket.
br
h4#descrip_title Rails
p#descrip_text  We use Rails as a Web Framework to do rapid web development.
br
h4#descrip_title Scheduling by Whenever gem + CRON
p#descrip_text  We use whenever gem to schedule in order to fetch all TLE from Celestrak Website to databases at 12:00 am everyday
br
h4#descrip_title Security / bcrypt
p#descrip_text  We use bcrypt to secure our user password by hashing.
br
h4#descrip_title PostgreSQL Datebase
p#descrip_text  We use PostgreSQL becauseit is one of the worldâ€™s most advanced open source database
br
h3#Application Frontend
br
h4#descrip_title WebGL Earth / OpenStreetMap
p#descrip_text  We use WebGL Earth and OpenStreetMap to show the users the position of the satellites on the map
br
h4#descrip_title Bootstrap
p#descrip_text  We use Bootstrap to design the UI and provide a suitable view to both mobile and desktop browser
br
h4#descrip_title Jquery
p#descrip_text  We use Jquery to update the latitude and longitude of the satellites and pin it into the map
br
h4#descrip_title Slim Gem
p#descrip_text  We use Slim to shorten the normal HTML format
br
h4#descrip_title Puma Application Server
p#descrip_text  We use Puma server for development process of the rails web application.
